<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-07T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-07T13:00:00-05:00" n="452" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d452">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/10–744: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-07T14:00:00-04:00">October 7, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>610. Should question of Millspaugh’s resignation again arise
                                Department desires that you make very clear to members of the
                                Financial Mission that the Department’s attitude as expressed in the
                                first paragraph of telegram 386 June 24 remains unchanged. It would
                                not be in the interests of the United States for them to resign in a
                                body.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>